related_items.title: The Polish organization Związek Strzelecki, 1935-38(?)
description: 85 photographic prints ; 22 x 16 cm. or smaller. | Prints and snapshots show activities of the Związek Strzelecki (Riflemen's Association), a paramilitary organization during the 1930's. Views of athletes running; playing basketball and participating in other sports. Views of military groups marching; laying wreath at national monument. Includes group of delegates visiting the 1935 international exhibition in Brussels at the inauguration of the Polish pavilion.
